                                    <div class="modal-body">
                                        <h3>Interview etiquette tips to leave good impressions on your interviewer!</h3>
                                        <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                                <p>
                                                    ■ Plan to arrive at the interview location at least 15-30 minutes early. This will make a good first impression
                                                    and ensures that you are not late. You can wait outside or in the waiting area if you are too early.
                                                </p>
                                                <p>
                                                    ■ Be polite and friendly to any staff you come into contact with. You might need to tell an employee that
                                                    you are there for an interview so that your interviewer knows you have arrived.
                                                </p>
                                                <p>
                                                    ■ Be ready to begin with a greeting, a smile and a handshake. Reach out your hand
                                                    and smile when you first enter the office, looking the interviewer in the eyes as you
                                                    introduce yourself.Your handshake should be firm – not too hard, but not limp. Practice this with a friend
                                                    before the interview.
                                                </p>
                                                <p>
                                                    ■ Be sure to smile occasionally, sit up straight in your chair and face the interviewer, try your best to sit still as you talk, and use an upbeat tone of voice if you can.
                                                </p>
                                                <p>
                                                    ■ Answer each question politely, even though the information may already be in your resume or application and be sure to thank the interviewer for their time and consideration
                                                </p>
